entry.title: Digest: Pashinyan and Putin scheduled to meet, more on COVID-19 in Armenia

media:group.media:title: Digest: Pashinyan and Putin scheduled to meet, more on COVID-19 in Armenia
media:group.media:description:
Armenian News - NEWS.am presents the daily digest of Armenia-related top news as of 11.10.21:
PUTIN https://news.am/eng/news/666821.html Russian President Vladimir Putin will meet with Prime Minister of Armenia Nikol Pashinyan and is also scheduled to meet with deputies of the new convocation of the Russian State Duma in the Kremlin. “The President will discuss with the parliament which issues are of paramount importance for the country…On the same day, Putin will have another meeting with Prime Minister of Armenia Nikol Pashinyan,” journalist Pavel Zarubin reported on the “Moscow. Kremlin. Putin” TV show aired on Russia 1 TV channel.
PROSECUTOR https://news.am/eng/news/666897.html A resident of Martakert, Artsakh (Nagorno-Karabakh), has been wounded and died on the spot from a shot fired from an Azerbaijani military position. Prior to the start of this agricultural work—and in consideration of this area being near the border with Azerbaijan—, Russian peacekeepers had arrived at the site to ensure the safety of the agricultural work. According to preliminary information, tepnants initially did not want to operate this tractor. But a Russian peacekeeper offered to sit with him in person in the cabin as an additional guarantee of safety. According to eyewitnesses, they made several rounds that way. On the same day, a criminal case was filed under the Artsakh Criminal Code article on "Murder committed by the motives of national, racial or religious hatred or religious fanaticism." An investigation is underway. After the incident, the agricultural work was stopped not only in that, but also in other border areas. The information on the killing of an Artsakh civilian by the Azerbaijani armed forces—and with a gross violation of the ceasefire—has been passed on to the representatives of the Russian Prosecutor General's Office representatives in Artsakh. The Prosecutor General's Office of Armenia will be consistent in the investigation of the murder of this Artsakh resident and Azerbaijan’s gross violation of the ceasefire.
ARCHITECT https://news.am/eng/news/666903.html Many monuments in Nagorno-Karabakh (Artsakh) are now under real threat of destruction. Russian architect Andrey Ivanov, who participated in the international conference entitled “Preservation of Historical and Cultural Heritage as a Means of Effective Dialogue among States,” said this to reporters in Yerevan on Monday. According to him, this conference is important from the point of view of drawing attention to the monuments of Artsakh.
CHILD https://news.am/eng/news/666873.html A tragic incident took place in Yerevan, shamshyan.com reported. At around 12:10am on Monday, the 911 emergency hotline received a call informing that there was a child's dead body under a concrete panel in an area. The rescuers and police officers who arrived at the scene found the dead body of E. E., 9, under a collapsed concrete stone in the aforesaid area. A number of forensic examinations have been ordered. Several people who were assembled at the scene said that the this area was owned by someone who did not follow the safety rules.
CATHOLICOS https://news.am/eng/news/666911.html Catholicos of All Armenians Karekin II on Monday will leave for Moscow, on a two-day visit, where he will meet with Kirill, the Patriarch of Moscow and All Russia, and attend a trilateral meeting between the religious leaders of the region.
IRAN https://news.am/eng/news/666824.html Deputy Minister of Roads and Municipal Development of Iran Kheyrula Khademi says Iran is ready to participate in the construction of a new transit road leading to Georgia through Armenia. “Armenia is preparing to create a new transit route from Iran to Georgia. We have declared the willingness to participate in the construction of that road,” Khademi said, ILNA agency cites. The official stated that this concerns the new corridor, besides the alternative Goris-Kapan road on which the parties have reached an agreement.
COVID-19 https://news.am/eng/news/666883.html As of Monday morning, 601 new cases of the coronavirus were confirmed in Armenia, and the total number of these cases has reached 272,957 in the country. Also, 26 more deaths from COVID-19 were registered, making the respective total 5,575 cases.
